29/10/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. 
Bush praised his Romanian counterpart, Ion Iliescu, for his strong leadership and applauded Romania's contribution to the international war on terrorism. 
The two leaders met privately in the Oval Office on Tuesday (28 October). 
White House Press Secretary Scott McClellan says they discussed bilateral relations, Romania's economic reforms, and co-operation in Iraq and Afghanistan. 
For his part, Iliescu said Romania has entered a new stage of partnership with the United States. 
(Act Media - 29/10/03; AP, Rompres - 28/10/03)
